### API 0: Get all images
# Used to verify the server is up and to find real IDs for testing.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/images

---

### API 1: Get one image by ID (Success)
# REPLACE the ID below with a real _id from your MongoDB
GET http://localhost:3000/api/images/69afbbceeed140c3db712b0c

### API 1: Get one image by ID (404 Not Found)
# Using a valid ObjectId format that doesn't exist in your DB.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/images/000000000000000000000000

---

### API 2: Rename image (Success - 204 No Content)
# REPLACE the ID below with a real _id from your MongoDB
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69afbbceeed140c3db712b0c
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "newName": "Majestic Husky"
}

### API 2: Rename image (404 Not Found)
# Triggered when the ID is valid but doesn't match any document.
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/111111111111111111111111
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "newName": "Ghost Cat"
}

### API 2: Rename image (400 Bad Request)
# Triggered because "newName" is missing from the JSON body.
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69afbbceeed140c3db712b0c
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "wrongKey": "This will fail"
}

### API 2: Rename image (413 Content Too Large)
# Triggered when the name exceeds the 100-character limit.
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/images/69afbbceeed140c3db712b0c
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "newName": "This is an extremely long name that is designed specifically to exceed the one hundred character limit imposed by the Lab 22a requirements to ensure the server correctly returns a 413 error code."
}